document.getElementById('searchInput').addEventListener('input', function () {
  const query = this.value.toLowerCase();
  const listings = document.querySelectorAll('.car-card');

  listings.forEach(card => {
    const text = card.textContent.toLowerCase();
    card.style.display = text.includes(query) ? 'block' : 'none';
  });
});
# Learning Dashboard

A responsive and professional dashboard interface for an online learning platform. Includes a video module, car search interface, course checklist, and chat sidebar.

## Features

- Responsive layout using Flexbox
- Searchable car listings
- Semantic HTML and modular CSS
- Clean and maintainable JavaScript

## Technologies

- HTML5
- CSS3
- JavaScript (ES6)

## Setup

1. Clone the repository
2. Open `index.html` in your browser
3. Customize assets and content as needed

